King Fisher.

72
00:05:39.007 --> 00:05:40.894
What's your business here,
Fisher?


73
00:05:40.927 --> 00:05:42.617
Come for my beeves.

74
00:05:42.655 --> 00:05:44.989
This here's an auction.

75
00:05:45.023 --> 00:05:47.292
You're welcome to bid
when the time comes.


76
00:05:47.326 --> 00:05:49.148
I bid 50.

77
00:05:49.182 --> 00:05:50.458
50 what?

78
00:05:50.494 --> 00:05:51.574
50 of them.

79
00:06:40.542 --> 00:06:42.452
Marshall, I don't
think you understand.


80
00:06:42.494 --> 00:06:45.909
Around here, I'm the law.

81
00:06:49.343 --> 00:06:51.764
Now, I'm taking my beeves home.

82
00:06:54.110 --> 00:06:56.761
I can't let you
take these cattle.


83
00:08:03.198 --> 00:08:04.573
All right, all of you,
fan out!


84
00:08:04.606 --> 00:08:07.323
Come on! Come on!

85
00:08:09.854 --> 00:08:11.032
Hyah!

86
00:08:12.830 --> 00:08:15.699
Come on, let's get out of here!

87
00:09:42.590 --> 00:09:44.859
Is anyone here?

88
00:09:58.174 --> 00:09:59.319
Don't move and I'll shoot!

89
00:10:00.446 --> 00:10:02.747
Don't move and you'll shoot?

90
00:10:02.782 --> 00:10:03.829
What does that mean?

91
00:10:03.870 --> 00:10:05.845
If I don't move,
you're going to shoot me?


92
00:10:05.886 --> 00:10:07.741
Who are you?
What are you doing here?


93
00:10:07.774 --> 00:10:10.424
My name is
Lincoln Rogers Dunnison.


94
00:10:10.462 --> 00:10:14.455
You understand, I'm not
one of the men who did this...


95
00:10:14.494 --> 00:10:17.941
so I'll be on my way.

96
00:10:24.350 --> 00:10:26.870
I can't lift it free.

97
00:10:26.910 --> 00:10:29.049
I can help you.

98
00:10:32.670 --> 00:10:34.907
Put down the gun.

99
00:10:37.918 --> 00:10:39.380
I'm from Missouri.

100
00:10:39.422 --> 00:10:41.309
We was on a cattle drive

101
00:10:41.342 --> 00:10:44.986
and stopped for supplies,
and we got ambushed.


102
00:10:45.022 --> 00:10:48.470
They stole all the cattle
and killed everybody.


103
00:10:48.510 --> 00:10:49.971
Didn't kill you.

104
00:10:50.014 --> 00:10:51.191
I was trapped...

105
00:10:51.230 --> 00:10:52.342
and they didn't see me

106
00:10:52.382 --> 00:10:54.008
and I'm damn lucky
that was the case


107
00:10:54.046 --> 00:10:55.639
otherwise, I'd be dead too.

108
00:10:55.678 --> 00:10:57.816
So, where you headed?

109
00:10:57.854 --> 00:10:59.064
Browusville.

110
00:10:59.102 --> 00:11:01.558
Browusville?
What's there?


111
00:11:01.598 --> 00:11:03.900
Texas Rangers are recruiting.

112
00:11:03.934 --> 00:11:05.625
Texas Rangers?!

113
00:11:05.662 --> 00:11:07.834
I'm going with you.

114
00:11:07.870 --> 00:11:09.593
We'll get them bandits.

115
00:11:09.630 --> 00:11:12.347
It's a long way to Browusville.

116
00:11:12.382 --> 00:11:14.487
I got a horse.

117
00:11:19.482 --> 00:11:21.587
Name's George Durham.

118
00:11:46.074 --> 00:11:47.536
Not so used

119
00:11:47.578 --> 00:11:49.520
to sleeping under the stars,
are you?


120
00:11:56.570 --> 00:12:01.077
Well...
there's nothing to it, really.


121
00:12:01.114 --> 00:12:03.536
Just, dig yourself
a little hip hole


122
00:12:03.578 --> 00:12:04.788
and then you fill a bandanna

123
00:12:04.826 --> 00:12:06.386
full of saw grass

124
00:12:06.426 --> 00:12:09.721
and stick that
underneath your head.


125
00:12:09.754 --> 00:12:12.721
It's the Lord's country,
Lincoln.


126
00:12:12.762 --> 00:12:16.656
Yeah... Lord's country.

127
00:12:16.697 --> 00:12:19.545
Land this beautiful...

128
00:12:19.577 --> 00:12:21.847
ain't no wonder

129
00:12:21.882 --> 00:12:23.889
everybody's killing over her.

130
00:12:28.154 --> 00:12:31.285
She's been here
a long time before us.


131
00:12:31.322 --> 00:12:32.467
She'll be here

132
00:12:32.506 --> 00:12:35.889
a long time to come.

133
00:12:35.930 --> 00:12:39.443
You are a philosopher,
George Durham.


134
00:12:42.394 --> 00:12:43.539
Hyah!

135
00:12:50.650 --> 00:12:51.927
Brownsville.

136
00:12:59.930 --> 00:13:01.840
We're going
to protect


137
00:13:01.882 --> 00:13:04.467
you people, least you can do

138
00:13:04.506 --> 00:13:05.880
is contribute supplies.

139
00:13:05.914 --> 00:13:07.440
You want a starving army?

140
00:13:07.482 --> 00:13:09.548
Who's going to keep
the crops safe then?


141
00:13:09.582 --> 00:13:10.678
You fellas there

142
00:13:10.713 --> 00:13:12.274
grab all the grub
you can carry.


143
00:13:12.314 --> 00:13:13.558
Get your irons and fall in.

144
00:13:13.593 --> 00:13:15.219
We're riding south
to kill bandits!


145
00:13:28.697 --> 00:13:30.520
Afternoon, Rangers.

146
00:13:32.602 --> 00:13:34.642
What's your business here?

147
00:13:34.682 --> 00:13:36.024
By order of the community

148
00:13:36.058 --> 00:13:38.131
I've got a vigilance committee
formed.


149
00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:40.537
Nary a Yankee, nigger
or Mexican among us.


150
00:13:40.570 --> 00:13:42.643
Unless you have
the authority of the state


151
00:13:42.682 --> 00:13:44.176
disband and disarm these men.

152
00:13:44.218 --> 00:13:45.744
They won't have it.

153
00:13:45.786 --> 00:13:47.193
We aim to protect our land.

154
00:13:47.226 --> 00:13:49.015
Men who want to protect
their land


155
00:13:49.050 --> 00:13:50.741
they can apply to hire from me.

156
00:13:50.777 --> 00:13:52.665
Governor's commissioned
the Rangers


157
00:13:52.697 --> 00:13:54.585
to do the protecting, mister.

158
00:13:54.617 --> 00:13:57.465
Now, you disband these men.

159
00:13:59.417 --> 00:14:01.719
You from San Antone?

160
00:14:02.714 --> 00:14:04.404
'Cause you sure as hell

161
00:14:04.442 --> 00:14:07.737
remind me
of this preacher there.


162
00:14:07.770 --> 00:14:10.225
It was some years ago...

163
00:14:10.266 --> 00:14:12.121
some preacher man.

164
00:14:12.153 --> 00:14:15.285
I don't recall no time
in San Antone.


165
00:14:15.322 --> 00:14:17.297
No, I suppose you don't.

166
00:14:23.321 --> 00:14:27.380
Men, you can keep your guns
to guard your homes


167
00:14:27.418 --> 00:14:30.352
but that means go home.

168
00:14:31.866 --> 00:14:34.648
I'll give you one minute
to take a vote.


169
00:14:51.354 --> 00:14:52.947
Hey, Preacher...

170
00:14:52.986 --> 00:14:54.327
vote's in.

171
00:15:00.218 --> 00:15:01.811
Preacher...

172
00:15:03.354 --> 00:15:04.547
say me last rites, Preacher

173
00:15:04.586 --> 00:15:05.695
before he takes me.

174
00:15:05.738 --> 00:15:07.609
I ain't no preacher.

175
00:15:12.250 --> 00:15:14.246
Company's making camp,
two nights in Brownsville.


176
00:15:14.282 --> 00:15:16.782
Any of you men interested
in taking on the star?


177
00:15:17.522 --> 00:15:20.186
West end of town's
where you'll find us.


178
00:15:20.722 --> 00:15:22.893
You look for me,
Leander McNelly


179
00:15:22.930 --> 00:15:24.042
or my associates

180
00:15:24.082 --> 00:15:26.122
Sergeant John Armstrong

181
00:15:26.162 --> 00:15:27.536
or Frank Bones.

182
00:15:36.402 --> 00:15:38.409
Hyah, hyah!

183
00:15:54.054 --> 00:15:56.836
Whoa-whoa. Whoa.

